{"version":3,"term":{"cols":100,"rows":30},"timestamp":1784192154,"command":"bash docs/trust-gate-demo.sh","env":{"SHELL":"/bin/zsh"}}
[0.094, "o", "\u001b[1;36m  agentstack — the zero-file trust gate\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;35m▎ You just cloned some repo. It declares MCP servers. What can its agent touch?\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.513, "o", "\u001b[2m$ agentstack mcp --auto-project   # (an agent asks the gateway what tools exist)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.520, "o", "  \u001b[2m→ untrusted, so:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.169, "o", "  No proxied tools available. This project (the-repo) is not trusted for auto mode, so none of its MCP servers are proxied (spawned or contacted). Ask a human to review the manifest \r\n"]
[0.003, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;35m▎ Nothing. Until YOU review it, none of its servers are spawned or even contacted.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.514, "o", "\u001b[2m$ agentstack trust .\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.543, "o", "    \u001b[33m▶\u001b[39m demo: runs `python3 /tmp/sandbox/server.py`\r\n  \u001b[32m✓\u001b[39m trusted at sha256:55276b88e1f99849ce9d965b83ff136e934b81a73d40ae76308a22bbcd75b51d.\r\n  Withdraw anytime with `agentstack trust --revoke`.\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;35m▎ You saw exactly what it would run, and trusted it (pinned to a content digest).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.516, "o", "\u001b[2m$ agentstack mcp --auto-project   # ask again, now trusted\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.604, "o", "  1 proxied tool(s) for 'echo':  - `demo__echo` — [via demo] Echo a message back   inspect: tools_search entity=\"demo__echo:tool\" \r\n"]
[0.006, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;35m▎ Now its tools are live through the gateway. The benign one is brokered end to end:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.510, "o", "\u001b[2m$ demo__echo { \"msg\": \"hi from a trusted repo\" }\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.599, "o", "  echo: hi from a trusted repo\r\n"]
[0.006, "o", "  \u001b[2m…and every brokered call lands in the audit log:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.049, "o", "  audit: {'server': 'demo', 'tool': 'echo', 'outcome': 'ok', 'ms': 52}\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;35m▎ But the repo's manifest also declared a FIREWALL. The sensitive tool is blocked:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.510, "o", "\u001b[2m$ demo__secret_read   # denied by [policy.tools] demo = \"!secret_read\"\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.620, "o", "  Error: demo__secret_read: call refused — denied by [policy.tools] rule \"!secret_read\"\r\n"]
[0.071, "o", "  audit: {'tool': 'secret_read', 'outcome': 'denied', 'detail': 'denied by [policy.tools] rule \"!secret_read\"'}\r\n"]
[0.002, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;35m▎ One more gate: your central library syncs machine-to-machine over git. Secrets don't.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.668, "o", "  \u001b[2msomeone pastes a REAL token into a shared server definition…\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m$ agentstack lib sync\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.532, "o", "  error: refusing to sync — a server definition holds a literal secret (use ${REF} instead, or pass --allow-secrets to override):\r\n      payments.toml: 'Authorization' has a literal value that looks like a secret — use ${REF} instead\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;35m▎ Blocked before it ever reaches a commit. Make it a ${REF} and it travels safely:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.529, "o", "\u001b[2m$ agentstack lib sync\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.995, "o", "  \u001b[32m✓\u001b[39m committed local changes\r\n  \u001b[32m✓\u001b[39m pushed to remote\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1;35m▎ That's the gate: clone → inert → review → trust → firewalled → audited — and secrets never travel.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.512, "o", "\u001b[1;32m  Nothing an agent can touch that you didn't review. Nothing secret ever pushed.\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.068, "x", "0"]
